# Registry & Systems

## Three-Phase Loop

```
update (order 0–19)   → input, AI, physics, animation
draw   (order 0)      → render pipeline (shadow + forward + post)
commit (order 0–100)  → flush input frame, record dt for FPS
```

Lower `order` runs first within a phase. Reserve bands:

| Band | Phase | Use |
|------|-------|-----|
| 0 | update | input toggles, debug |
| 5 | update | camera orbit / pivot |
| 10 | update | character physics |
| 20 | update | animation sampling |
| 0 | draw | render pipeline |
| 0 | commit | input.commitFrame() |
| 100 | commit | dt capture |

## Component Queries — Always use `registry.view()`

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — cached, only entities with this component
for (const e of registry.view('character')) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — iterates all entities every frame
for (const e of registry.all()) {
  const c = e.components['character'];
  if (!c) continue;
  ...
}
```

`view(key)` returns a cached `ReadonlyArray<Entity>` invalidated only on create/deregister.
Call `registry.invalidateView()` if you add a component to an existing entity mid-frame.

## Static Colliders

Pass static colliders explicitly to `installCharacterSystem` and `installCameraSystem` — do not query them per frame.

```typescript
const staticColliders: Collider[] = [];
const c = await instantiateStaticProp(...);
if (c) staticColliders.push(c);

installCharacterSystem(registry, input, staticColliders);
installCameraSystem(registry, pipeline, input, staticColliders);
```

Static colliders never move — building the list once during bootstrap is correct.

## System Installer Pattern

Every system is a standalone `install*System(registry, ...deps)` function:

```typescript
export const installSpiderSystem = (registry: Registry, staticColliders: Collider[]) => {
  registry.addAction('update', (ctx) => {
    for (const e of registry.view('spiderAI')) {
      // ...
    }
  }, 15); // order between camera (5) and animation (20)
};
```

## Entity Composition

Entities are plain objects; components are direct property assignments:

```typescript
const e = registry.create();
e.components['transform'] = createTransform();
e.components['spiderAI'] = createSpiderAI();
```

Components are data-only. Behaviour lives exclusively in system installers.
